					<head>Liturgy</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n79090052" rend="visible">
						<summary>A daily prayer book (sidur), Italian rite, with the books of Psalms, Proverbs, Job, Five Scrolls, and the Hafṭarot for the entire year in the margins.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/n79090052">
							<locus from="1r" to="479v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Sidur</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">סדור</title>
							<note>
								<p>The margin contains the Psalms (149), folio 10r; the book of Proverbs, folio 134v; Job, folio 180r; Ruth, folio 234r; the Song of Songs, folio 242v; Ecclesiastes, folio 251v; Lamentations, folio 271r; Esther, folio 281v; the Hafṭarot for the whole year (preceded and followed by the benedictions), folio 303r.</p>
								<p>Folios 4r-9r contain an index of the Psalms.</p>
								<p>The margin of folios 4r-5r contains the times for reading the Song of Songs, Avot, Ruth, Psalms, Proverbs, Job, Daniel, Ezra-Nahemiah, and Ecclesiastes.</p>
								<p>For further bibliography see: <ref target="Freimann_1950" type="page">231-342</ref>, <ref target="JJA" type="number">3-4 (1977)</ref>, pp. 58-73 (pp. 68-69); <ref target="Metzger_1982" type="page">304</ref>; <ref target="Tahan_2007" type="page">74</ref>; <ref target="Tamani_1985" type="page">103-113</ref>
, (pp. 109-111).
</p>
							</note>
							<colophon xml:lang="he">נשלמו כל הפטרות והסידו' מכל השנה יתברך שוכן מעונה. אמן. וזה נכתב ונשלם הנה בעיר <name type="place">בירטינורו </name>היום יום <date calendar="Hebrew">ו' ראש חדש אייר שנת חמשת אלפים ומאה וחמשים לבריאת עולם</date>. השם יזכינו להגות בו לעד אמן. וחלקי המחוקק יהיה צפון עם מצדיקי הרבים ככוכבים לעולם ועד. אמן: <locus n="479r"/>
							</colophon>
							<decoNote type="miniature">1 full-page miniature of a coat of arms, in colours and gold.<locus n="2v"/>
							</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="border">1 full foliate border in colours and gold.<locus n="10r"/>
							</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="border">Numerous texts in decorated frames and inhabited by birds, animals, hybrids, in colours. <locus from="3v" to="9r"/>
							</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="initial">Many initial-word panels with pen-flourishing inhabited by birds and hybrids, in colours.
</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="marginal">Many pen-flourishing and foliate motifs around passages sometimes inhabited by hybrids and birds.</decoNote>
